# UI & Design Guidelines

## Theme System

The app uses a layered theme: build-time `theme.json` → runtime Supabase business colors.

- Access colors via `useColors()` hook from `src/theme/ThemeProvider`
- Access branding (logo, company name) via `useBranding()` hook
- Access fonts via `useFonts()` hook
- Full theme context via `useTheme()`

### Color Tokens (ThemeColors interface)

`primary`, `secondary`, `accent`, `background`, `surface`, `text`, `textSecondary`, `border`, `success`, `warning`, `error`, `info`

## Styling Rules

- Use `StyleSheet.create()` for all styles — no inline style objects in JSX
- Use theme color tokens, never hardcode colors (e.g. `colors.primary` not `'#007AFF'`)
- Use `LinearGradient` from expo-linear-gradient for gradient backgrounds
- Animations: use `react-native-reanimated` for performant animations
- Bottom sheets: use `@gorhom/bottom-sheet`
- Icons: use `lucide-react-native` as primary icon library, `@expo/vector-icons` as fallback

## Component Patterns

- Functional components only — no class components
- Extract reusable UI into `components/` folder
- Screens should compose from smaller components, not contain all UI inline
- Modals: use BottomSheet or React Native Modal — follow existing patterns in `components/`
- Loading states: show skeleton/spinner, never a blank screen
- Error states: show user-friendly message with retry option

## Design Aesthetic — מראה כללי

- Modern, clean, rounded corners (borderRadius: 12-16 for cards)
- Soft shadows for elevation on cards
- Generous padding and spacing (16-24 units)
- Gradient hero sections on home screens
- Card-based layouts for lists (appointments, services, products)
- Floating action buttons for primary actions (e.g. book appointment "+")
- Blur effects (`expo-blur`) for overlays and modals
